text: @LgSOS Yeah. Interesting and well done study and fits with what we'd expect based on observations of abundant recombination in seasonal coronaviruses: https://t.co/xaXQ00eSqO

@SSCougFan I agree that it should be easy for someone to assess their individual level of protection. People who've had COVID and have had two doses may not need a third. Having assay available would be informative for some individual's decision making.

Here, I think of @alexismadrigal's piece on the implications of a positive COVID test (https://t.co/Lk4g5q2REs). It's crazy to me that we're saying to healthy younger individuals they must isolate for 10 days after a positive test, but that they're not eligible for a booster. 3/6
